{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Rows with missing required fields are rejected and appear in the dead-letter queue with the original row number.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is between CSV parsing/validation and DLQ handoff. A unit test of validator logic alone can pass while row-index propagation or DLQ serialization fails when modules are wired together.","test_description":"Run pipeline on a small CSV fixture with known missing required fields and mixed valid rows, using real parser + validator + DLQ writer (local queue/table/file). Assert invalid rows are absent from normalized output, present in DLQ, and each DLQ record contains the exact original CSV row number.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The transformation correctly converts date strings in multiple formats (ISO 8601, US, European) to a single canonical format.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This behavior is transformation logic at a single function/object boundary. No module handoff or I/O is required to expose parsing/normalization bugs.","test_description":"Test the date-normalization function directly with table-driven cases for ISO 8601, US (MM/DD/YYYY), and European (DD/MM/YYYY) inputs, including ambiguous dates and invalid strings. Assert canonical output (or explicit error) per case.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.9,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A CSV file with 500,000 rows completes processing within the configured timeout without running out of memory.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This is a runtime/resource behavior dependent on process memory usage, GC behavior, and wall-clock execution under realistic load. Lower-level tests cannot reliably reveal OOM/timeout failures.","test_description":"Execute the pipeline as a real process against a generated 500,000-row CSV and real local sinks/config, with the production timeout setting. Measure completion time and peak RSS; fail if timeout is exceeded or memory crosses the configured limit/OOM occurs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.89,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When the S3 bucket returns a transient 503 error, the pipeline retries with exponential backoff rather than failing the entire batch.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Real failure often occurs at HTTP/SDK boundary (status-to-exception mapping, retry middleware, backoff timing). Pure mocks can hide these issues by bypassing real client behavior.","test_description":"Point the pipeline’s S3 client to a local HTTP S3-compatible endpoint/test server that returns 503 for initial requests then 200. Run ingestion and assert: retries occurred, backoff intervals increase approximately exponentially, and batch ultimately succeeds without full-batch abort.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.22,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Rows successfully written to PostgreSQL are not duplicated if the pipeline is restarted mid-batch.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Idempotency across restart depends on durable DB state plus restart/process lifecycle behavior. Integration tests without real restart can miss duplication caused by checkpoint/transaction ordering in actual process termination/recovery.","test_description":"Run pipeline against real PostgreSQL with a unique business key/idempotency key. Interrupt the process mid-batch (e.g., SIGTERM/kill), restart it with same input, then assert final row count equals unique input rows and no duplicate keys exist.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.24,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
